                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d50">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">500.A15A4 General Committee (Arms)/159:
                    Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        American Delegate</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Wilson</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1935-03-29T18:00:00-05:00"
                            >March 29, 1935—6 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>492. Your 1020, March 21, 4 p.m. Navy Department states advance notice of naval
                    construction would be to the advantage of the United States and therefore is
                    favorable in principle to such an idea. You may so inform Captain Deleuze in
                    confidence.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
